annotation.TEXT: Hey, there's a mushroom up here, too. Nice.
There doesn't appear to be anything up here, and the timer's yelling at me to hurry up, so let's go through the boss door, and fight...
MOOOOOONNNNN!!!!!! MUST GET!!! I MUST HAVE THE MOOOOONNN!!!!
More sparky-thingie dodging...
Well, let's see if I can find a way to "break" the level. Maybe there's an invisible block around here...
Next time, I'll explore the level above Kaizo Breaker. To be continued...
Aha!
Up next, we have a linear level, Shell Factory. Hopefully, it won't take nearly as long to complete...
Hello!
Well, there's those red star blocks. Let's just take a peek over there...
I'm betting this part over here is the section I skipped, so I should probably head left now.
Okay, that was an odd way to get a kill, but whatever.
Okay, seriously, stop feeding the muncher! But at least I found a weak point in the cement box!
This part gets insane. There's a turn block that looks like it needs to be hit, but I couldn't seem to reach it with the ice block. Fortunately, I didn't have to hit it anyway.
Let's see exactly what I skipped when I did that six-block high jump here.
Now, this looks like it could get tricky!
Well...
That's it? Suddenly I'm done? Wow... And that makes two levels in a row that I've cleared without dying. Awesome!
Okay, let's not waste that good fortune!
Gonna grab me a shell for protection, just in case.
I like the Lego look of this place. Also, the music is nice and cheery too. What song is this anyway? It sounds familiar... I should know this one!
Next up is Kaizo Breaker. Ooh, sounds interesting!
But what about that door I didn't explore? Is there anything more that I should look for?
Also, this key here can rest on a couple of invisible blocks (ones that Mario can't stand on), which makes this part easier than I expected.
Whoops. Well, I should still be able to do this.
It's the latest app to hit the market, the iBlocks!
As I thought, a wall that I can run up has appeared.
Now, you might be thinking, "It would be cool to see a TAS of the Kaizo paths in that level!"
Holy crap! Now, that's gotta be a miracle!
Huh, so shells don't work on those sparky things. (Or maybe they're like Thwimps, and shells might work, depending on sprite slots, but I'm not going to fiddle with that now.)
Yep, sure looks like it.
YESSS!!!! THE MOOOONNN IS MIIIIINNNNE!!!!
Hmm... Those jumps to the right don't actually look that tough, but I'm going to see if I can find a "break" somewhere back here.
Anything special up here?
Shell-kicking koopas... How fitting.
This P-switch is probably needed to "break" another Kaizo section.
Ha! Your upside-down purple mushrooms can't stop me now!
Yep, definitely sounds interesting!
That's a forced hit, but I can at least keep my other mushroom for now.
Umm... Maybe I shouldn't have scrolled the screen up here...
There are two doors, but which one should I enter? Well, I randomly decided to try the door on the left first.
Just a few shell beams, that's all. Hmm... What's with that gap in the upper-right?
Whoa! I think I just barely avoided getting fried there!
Yeah, I could've certainly made those jumps. Well, let's go back for the P-switch. I'm sure I'll need it soon...
This may turn into a blind jump here...
Hello, and welcome back to EVW! Last time, I eventually found a way through the complex level, Shaded Volcano.
Okay, that joke was lame. Hey, there's a star, but it appears to be sealed in a cement box...
Saw that one coming a mile away!
Oh, really? Yes, really. Is there any way to shrink myself around here, like with a muncher, perhaps?
Okay, I'm good, and I can easily slide-kill the saw. I bet it was intended that I use the P-switch to dump the saw in the pit, though.
I just know there's gonna be like 55 people telling me what this song is now... (No, you don't have to do that. I know it's Shy Guy's Toy Box from Paper Mario!)
Yeah, definitely push it now.
I'm going to try to avoid stepping into the shell beams' paths as much as possible.
Epic moment.
Now, let's see what goodies lie beyond this Aqua Switch bridge...
Okay, good. There was way more than enough invincibility time.
More shell beam dodging...
What's over here, I wonder?
I wonder if there's anything in these unturnable turn blocks...
Anyways, those spark-looking things look dangerous. You can bounce off of them with a spin jump, but I bet touching them in any other way will result in Mario being electrocuted!
There must be something special for me over there if I've already hit all four Aqua Switches. Well, let's go hit the last Aqua Switch now!
Ha! You thought you could surprise me there? Well, you thought wrong!
This part isn't too tricky if you're patient. (I wonder how Goron50 would do here...)
Nothing special I guess. Well, let's end this video with Mario getting shell beamed!
No? I guess that would be why the side exit is enabled. Still, why not provide a muncher or something to shrink myself with?
TAS run initiated.
A falling key? Wow, I wonder what kind of trickery the Kaizo path would've had me going through down there...
The muncher goes, "OM NOM NOM".
Oh? And it looks like I needed the P-switch to get this springboard as well, which I'm sure is used for the next "break".
Cough. Ahem. Moving along...
That door looks kind of flashy...
Well, so much for that shell shield.
Shell-shooting cannons... Okay... At least I can stomp these shells with no problem. (I'm guessing they're actually diagonal Bullet Bills.)
It looks like I'm supposed to go down here, but... that ledge above is just six tiles up, so I think I can take a shortcut here!
I probably shouldn't be wasting time grabbing coins over there...
Well, let's back up and find out what's beyond the right door!
Aha! Found it! Going up!
Were all those wall jumps really necessary?
Nothing! Then, what's the point of that path?
Naw, I'm just kidding! I gotta go back and do it for real. Obviously, the side exit was enabled there for some reason.
Koopa hopping over shell beams...
Hmm... I wonder if there's anything interesting up here?
I'm pretty sure those "shell beams" will be bad news if I touch them, so let's not touch them!
I think I want the upper route. I hope I didn't waste too much time there!
And that's a different way to finish the level, but there's one more piece of unfinished business...
Okay, back in non-TAS land, now that I'm small, I'm going back to Shell Factory.
Made it! Huzzah!
Looks kind of tough, although I can see a mushroom over there...
Still not too tough... yet.
Okay, level's complete! Let's move onto the next level!
Uh, oh! Watch out!
Ooh, I get to bring an iBlock with me! ...Or not. Oh, well.
...nothing! There's no boss here. Oh, well.
Yeah, I could've fallen into the pit that was there, but I don't feel like suiciding right now, so I'll just move on, and I'll come back later when I'm small.
Blue shell-less koopas are weird.
There are a couple turn blocks hidden below the screen here. Also, I couldn't find a way to avoid touching those munchers while super.
I don't need two shells, however.
Auto-scrolling... Uh, oh. (Also, I have an interesting score right now.)
I probably should use the P-switch here anyway.
A goal sphere. That's it. While that doesn't surprise me too much, I thought there'd also be something like a 1-up as well...
